element.definition: An operation to request a NDC Labeler code for a registrant or private Labeler organization.

constraint.human: All FHIR elements must have a @value or children

element.definition: Unique id for the element within a resource (for internal references). This may be any string value that does not contain spaces.

slicing.description: Extensions are always sliced by (at least) url

element.definition: May be used to represent additional information that is not part of the basic definition of the element. To make the use of extensions safe and manageable, there is a strict set of governance  applied to the definition and use of extensions. Though any implementer can define an extension, there is a set of requirements that SHALL be met as part of the definition of the extension.
element.comment: There can be no stigma associated with the use of extensions by any application, project, or standard - regardless of the institution or jurisdiction that uses or defines the extensions.  The use of extensions is what allows the FHIR specification to retain a core level of simplicity for everyone.

element.definition: A unique identifier of an instance of a Labeler Code Request operation.
The time when this request operation was created.
A unique identifier of a specific group of Labeler Code Request operations.
A string identifying a specific version of the Labeler Code Request operation group.
The organization that is requesting the NDC Labeler Code.
The Dun & Bradstreet number assigned to the Labeler organization headquarters.
The NDC Labeler code assigned by the FDA to Labeler organization.
The business name of the Labeler organization.
The Labeler organization's address.
The person at the Labeler Organization to contact about this Labeler request.
The name of the Labeler contact person.
The address of the Labeler contact person.
The telephone number for the Labeler contact person.
The email address for the Labeler contact person.
An organization that acts on the behalf of a Labeler that is not located in the US.
The Dun & Bradstreet number assigned to the organization acting as the labeler's US agent.
The name of the organization acting as the Labeler's US agent.
The telephone number for the organization acting as the Labeler's US agent.
The email address for the organization acting as the Labeler's US agent.
Various business operations that the Labeler organization performs.
A code representing the specific business operation that the Labeler organization can perform.
A code that gives more information about the business operation that the Labeler organization can perform.
